Follow these rules when writing Typescript code:

- Avoid using any or unknown, use strong typing whenever possible.
- Avoid using non-null assertions (!).

## Functions

On functions, when reasonable, use JSDoc comments with a brief description, .\n,
tags, and examples when simple enough (@example add(1, 2) // => 3). Always make
sure JSDoc comments are up to date.
<example>
```
/**
 * Fetch a single ArtifactEnrichment by id.
 *
 * @param {string} id — The id of the ArtifactEnrichment
 * @returns {Promise<ArtifactEnrichment | null>} — Promise resolving to the ArtifactEnrichment model or null
 */
public artifactEnrichmentById(
    id: string,
): Promise<ArtifactEnrichment | null> { ... }
```
</example>

## Classes

On classes, use block comments.
<example>
```
/**
 * Handles user authentication and session management.
 */
class AuthService { ... }
```
</example>
    